As a mother, I’ve always believed that care doesn’t stop at home, it extends into the spaces we build and the people we grow with.

Over the years, I’ve seen that same bond form with the women I’ve mentored and worked with through shared purpose, belief, and quiet encouragement.
We may not have called it motherhood, but the care was real. The pride, just as deep.

#MothersDay

latestPosts.caption:
Celebrating 40 wonderful years of someone who is BEYOND beautiful.

Pallavi, a daughter, a mom, a one-in-a-million kind of soul…
These 40 years? Pure magic.

You’re not just Vidhaan and Vardaan’s mom,
You’re the heart and soul of every kid in the family.
Vaania, Ameera, Avyaan, Avina, Yuvraj, 
Each one has felt your love in their own special way.

But you’re so much more than just “mom.”
You’re the daughter who makes us proud.
The sister who’s there no matter what.
The wife with a heart full of love.
And the friend who just “gets it” and feels like home.

Pallavi, you’ve always been, and continue to be, beyond beautiful. Inside and out, through actions and in words; and hope you always shine bright!

With all our love, pride and blessings.
Vandana & Mukesh
